	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Idea for cell-shaded FMV on the NES</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The best part is if you're dealing with monochrome RLE predictors, you don't need to signal what bit you are currently using.  You know it will transition from 1 to 0, then 0 to 1.  You only need the initial state and the lengths.  Then you're just encoding a bunch of numbers (RLE lengths) and nothing else.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
